What failed and why (diagnosis)
From the last CI log, the remaining compiler errors are grouped into a few categories:

1) Assigning UUID to String fields
Examples:
- CartCheckoutProcessor.java, OrderCreationProcessor.java, ShipmentTriggerProcessor.java:
  - Code sets id using UUID.randomUUID() while the entity id fields are String.
  - Error: incompatible types: UUID cannot be converted to String

  Fix: convert UUID to String when assigning to String id fields:
  - Replace UUID.randomUUID() with UUID.randomUUID().toString()

2) Product price type mismatch
- Product.java currently has price as Double.
- Some processors (e.g., ProductImportProcessor, ValidateOrderProcessor, others) compare price with BigDecimal.ZERO and call product.getPrice().compareTo(BigDecimal.ZERO) — that requires price to be BigDecimal.
- Error: incompatible types: BigDecimal cannot be converted to Double

  Fix: change Product.price from Double to BigDecimal and import java.math.BigDecimal. Also review any code that creates/sets product price.

3) Missing product version field (getVersion/setVersion)
- InventoryReservationProcessor references product.getVersion() / setVersion(...), but Product.java did not have a version field.
- Error: cannot find symbol: method getVersion(), setVersion(...)

  Fix: add an Integer version field to Product (Lombok @Data will generate getter/setter).

4) Shipment provider vs carrier naming mismatch
- ShipmentTriggerProcessor calls shipment.setProvider("SIMULATED_SHIPPER"); but Shipment.java defines carrier or lacks provider setter.
- Error: cannot find symbol: method setProvider(String)

  Fix: make Shipment.java include a provider field (or change the processors to use setCarrier). Easiest: add provider field to Shipment as an alias to carrier.

